OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FMarch had been released from prison on
OL,7,Fa life licence in 2013 after he was
OL,8,Fimprisoned for fatally stabbing a
OL,9,Fseventeen year old in the neck at a
OL,10,FMcDonalds in South London.
OL,12,FHe was recalled to jail later that
OL,13,Fyear after he stamped on the stomach
OL,14,Fof another pregnant girlfriend in
OL,15,FJuly. March was released again in
OL,16,FFebruary 2018.
OL,18,FHe also had convictions for assault
OL,19,Fand criminal damage in 1995.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FThe Solicitor General referred his
OL,7,Fsecond life sentence to the Court of
OL,8,FAppeal, with barristers telling a
OL,9,Fhearing on Thursday that March should
OL,10,Fhave been given a whole life order.
OL,12,FMarch also challenged the length of
OL,13,Fhis sentence, with his barristers
OL,14,Fclaiming it was "manifestly excessive".
OL,16,FIn a ruling, Lord Justice Edis,
OL,17,Fsitting with Mr Justice Cavanagh and
OL,18,FJudge Alice Robinson, said: "The
OL,19,Fsentence was unduly lenient.
OL,26,@vD@QOUvD@fO]zD@]OU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,F"We quash it, and we quash the minimum
OL,7,Fterm order that the judge made, and
OL,8,Fsubstitute in its place a whole life
OL,9,Forder, which means that the offender
OL,10,Fwill never be released."
OL,12,FAfter being told he would die behind
OL,13,Fbars, March, who watched Thursday's
OL,14,Fproceedings via a videolink from HMP
OL,15,FBelmarsh in London, addressed members
OL,16,Fof Ms Odysseos' family in court.
OL,18,FHe said: "I just want to say that I am
OL,19,Fsorry."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@XO]zD@JOU{D@GO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FMarch's trial at the Old Bailey heard
OL,7,Fthat Ms Odysseos, who was in the early
OL,8,Fstages of pregnancy with her third
OL,9,Fchild at the time of her death, knew
OL,10,Fabout his murder conviction, with
OL,11,Fsafeguarding checks made by probation
OL,12,Fservices.
OL,14,FHe admitted her murder on the seventh
OL,15,Fday of his trial after an expert no
OL,16,Flonger supported his defence of
OL,17,Fdiminished responsibility.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FTom Little KC, for the Solicitor
OL,7,FGeneral, told the Court of Appeal in
OL,8,Fwritten submissions that March and Ms
OL,9,FOdysseos had been in a relationship
OL,10,Ffor around four months, during which
OL,11,Ftime March attacked her and stopped
OL,12,Fher from talking to family and friends.
OL,14,FThey also argued about her pregnancy,
OL,15,Fincluding in the hours before Alana's
OL,16,Fmurder.
OL,18,FThe pregnant woman was heard saying "I
OL,19,Fdon't want to kill my baby". She was
OL,20,Flater seen outside the property,
OL,21,Fclutching her right side.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FBleeding from multiple stab wounds to
OL,7,Fher body, she pointed at March and
OL,8,Fshouted:
OL,10,F"Shaine stabbed me, he stabbed me.
OL,11,FHelp, help."
OL,13,FMarch walked away as Ms Odysseos died
OL,14,Foutside her home.
OL,16,FShe had suffered stab wounds to her
OL,17,Fchest, stomach, pelvis, shoulders,
OL,18,Fbuttocks, right arm, thighs and lower
OL,19,Flegs.
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@LO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FBefore throwing his mobile phone in a
OL,7,Fdrain, March recorded a voice note
OL,8,Fsaying:
OL,10,F"Mum, I just killed a woman, and I'm
OL,11,Fgoing back to jail."
OL,13,FSentencing him, Mr Justice Murray said
OL,14,Fthe murder involved "prolonged and
OL,15,Fexcessive violence" but that he did
OL,16,Fnot consider the case to be one where
OL,17,F"the need for lifelong imprisonment is
OL,18,Fclear beyond doubt".
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@TO]vD@UOUwD@SO]yD@AOUzD@SO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FHe based this on four factors,
OL,7,Fincluding that March suffered a
OL,8,Ftraumatic brain injury when he was a
OL,9,Fteenager, which affected his ability
OL,10,Fto regulate his emotions, and that
OL,11,Fboth murders were "apparently
OL,12,Fspontaneous".
OL,14,FBut Mr Little told the Court of Appeal
OL,15,Fon Thursday that a whole life order
OL,16,Fwas "just punishment" and that there
OL,17,Fwas a "constellation of aggravating
OL,18,Ffeatures" in the case.
OL,26,@sD@SOUtD@LO]xD@EOUxD@UO]yD@GOUzD@IO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,406,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1774703465
OL,3,CDouble murderer given whole life order
OL,4,Cafter sentence ruled too lenient
OL,6,FIn court, he said: "Properly analysed,
OL,7,Fthis case should never have left the
OL,8,Fcategorisation as a whole life order
OL,9,Fcase."
OL,11,FSandip Patel KC, for March, told the
OL,12,Fcourt that the sentence was reached in
OL,13,Fa "fair and balanced manner".
OL,15,FHe also said that March's sentence
OL,16,Fshould be reduced on the grounds of
OL,17,Fhis traumatic brain injury, stating
OL,18,Fthat Mr Justice Murray "did not give
OL,19,Fit the fullest regard".
OL,26,@nD@TOUqD@FO]uD@COUuD@\O]zD@XOU{D@VO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/11
